Nine more COVID-19 patients have been discharged from the Federal Capital Territory Administration (FCTA) Isolation Centre, located at the University of Abuja Teaching Hospital (UATH), Gwagwalada-Abuja. The Chief Medical Director (CMD) of the hospital, Prof  Bissallah  Ekele explained that seven patients were discharged late Tuesday night, while another two were discharged on Wednesday. “We are happy to announce that seven patients were discharged from UATH Isolation Center, Gwagwalada today. The remaining ones are clinically stable and responding well to treatment. To God be the glory.” Recall that the FCT Administration had earlier discharged 11 persons in two batches, while assuring that others who were in stable condition would soon be discharged.  The total of 20 patients has so far been discharged from the isolation centre. 